st-fit planetary model that is slightly preferred over the\nbest-fit binary-source model. However, when allowed for a change in the color\nduring the perturbation, we find that the binary-source model yields a\nsignificantly better fit and thus the degeneracy is clearly resolved. This\nevent not only signifies the importance of considering various interpretations\nof short-term anomalies, but also demonstrates the importance of multi-band\ndata for checking the possibility of false-positive planetary signals.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Aug 2013 06:34:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
